INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4,2,'2019-01-31 19:16:20','2019-01-31 19:16:20','','fdj_logo','','inherit','open','closed','','fdj_logo','','','2019-01-31 19:16:20','2019-01-31 19:16:20','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fdj_logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(5,2,'2019-01-31 19:16:30','2019-01-31 19:16:30','','fdj_logo-retina','','inherit','open','closed','','fdj_logo-retina','','','2019-01-31 19:16:30','2019-01-31 19:16:30','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/fdj_logo-retina.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(15,2,'2017-11-17 12:05:12','2017-11-17 12:05:12','Thanks for registering!\n\nTo complete the activation of your account and site, go to the following link: <a href=\"{{{activate-site.url}}}\">{{{activate-site.url}}}</a>.\n\nAfter you activate, you can visit your site at <a href=\"{{{user-site.url}}}\">{{{user-site.url}}}</a>.','[{{{site.name}}}] Activate {{{user-site.url}}}','Thanks for registering!\n\nTo complete the activation of your account and site, go to the following link: {{{activate-site.url}}}\n\nAfter you activate, you can visit your site at {{{user-site.url}}}.','publish','closed','closed','','site-name-activate-user-site-url','','','2017-11-17 12:05:12','2017-11-17 12:05:12','',0,'https://aardvark.ghostpool.com/members-directory/?post_type=bp-email&amp;p=15',0,'bp-email','',0),(21,2,'2015-03-26 00:00:00','2015-03-26 00:00:00','<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you’ve been at the same job for a while now, and have not received any kind of promotion or raise, it’s common to wonder what you’re doing wrong. However, you might not be doing anything wrong at all! Advancing your career is not just about making yourself look good. You need to pace yourself, observe and learn from those around you, and be mindful of how to use your leadership and other unique skills to leave your mark on the company.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:more -->\n<!--more-->\n<!-- /wp:more -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><br>Networking Is Step 1 for a Promotion</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A lot of the time, people believe that getting promoted or getting a raise is all about standing out as a star within the company. While it’s important to make sure that you’re presenting your best self at the office, you can never be successful alone! It’s crucial to be a team player because it is the support of your coworkers that helps enable you to create more opportunities for yourself within the company.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Turn up your job search with our guide <a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/networking-complete-guide/\">Everything You Need to Know to Master Networking</a>.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Being successful in the workplace is really dependent upon <a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/how-to-make-the-most-of-your-job/\">establishing yourself as a team player</a>. It’s harder to be successful alone. You’ll find that by garnering the support of your coworkers, you will feel like you’re able to make more of an impact on the company and get noticed at work without being a self-promoter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><br>\"Silent Influencers\" get promotions</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It’s the individuals who are considered \"silent influencers\" are most likely to get promoted. These people are confident, but they only speak up when it matters, when they really want their voice to be heard. These individuals make more of an impact on the company than those who are distracted by positioning themselves and playing office politics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you want to see a promotion or raise in your near future, you must be quick to see and seize opportunities. However, flaunting your success is a surefire way to make your team members question whether you are a team player, or whether your intentions are primarily self-serving.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Rather than flaunting your success, you should consistently exceed the expectations of your job description. By being quick to see and seize opportunities, you can expand your influence throughout the organization, and your hard work will speak for itself – no need for self-promotion!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><br>Be a Mentor</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Those who help their colleagues succeed are showing that they are confident, trustworthy, and have solid leadership skills. The more opportunities you take to help others, the more they will help you. Creating mutual trust is a crucial element for any team.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While it’s important to develop friendships within the office – it is where you spend most of your time! – remember to keep it professional. While you\'re working hard on deepening relationships with co-workers, resist the temptation to let these them become intimate. The best protection against charges of inappropriate behavior is to ask \"what would Aretha Franklin do?\" (Answer: RESPECT!)</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Being an incredible mentor will help you to stand out around the office. It could even help you to get that promotion you\'re after. Here are <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/jacquelynsmith/2013/05/17/how-to-become-a-great-mentor/#7b0836ca4f59\">some more tips</a> about how to become a better mentor. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2><br>Always Be Yourself</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Last, but certainly not least, always be yourself! This is an almost guaranteed way to get noticed by your coworkers. While you should always conduct yourself professionally, it’s okay to let your personality shine through. Most people forget how far just being yourself can go!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Figure out how you best fit within the organization. Then, trust yourself enough to quickly see and seize opportunities in order to expand your influence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Do your best to consistently exceed the expectations of your job description. Be a ‘silent influencer’, and help your colleagues succeed! The success of the company as a whole is dependent upon everyone helping each other. So it’s crucial to be a team player if you’d like to climb the corporate ladder!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And remember, nobody is perfect! In the words of the great Vince Lombardi, “Nobody’s Perfect. But if you strive for perfection, you’ll catch excellence.”</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Good Luck from your friends at FindDreamJobs.com!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:separator -->\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\"/>\n<!-- /wp:separator -->','How Do Managers Decide Who Gets a Promotion','','publish','open','open','','find-job-promotion','','','2019-07-11 21:46:12','2019-07-11 21:46:12','',0,'http://www2.finddreamjobs.com/2015/03/26/find-job-promotion/',4,'post','',0),(34,2,'2017-11-17 12:25:26','2017-11-17 12:25:26','','header-bg','','inherit','open','closed','','header-bg','','','2017-11-17 12:25:26','2017-11-17 12:25:26','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/header-bg.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(35,2,'2017-11-17 14:42:26','2017-11-17 14:42:26','','Member Search','','publish','closed','closed','','members-search','','','2017-11-17 14:42:26','2017-11-17 14:42:26','',0,'https://aardvark.ghostpool.com/members-directory/?post_type=bps_form&amp;p=35',0,'bps_form','',0),(37,2,'2017-11-17 15:35:53','2017-11-17 15:35:53','','person-11','','inherit','open','closed','','person-11','','','2017-11-17 15:35:53','2017-11-17 15:35:53','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/person-11.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(38,2,'2017-11-17 15:36:31','2017-11-17 15:36:31','','person-3','','inherit','open','closed','','person-3','','','2017-11-17 15:36:31','2017-11-17 15:36:31','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/person-3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(370,2,'2016-03-04 16:45:41','2016-03-04 16:45:41','For most employers, both hard and soft skills are equally important. Although hard skills are necessary to do your job, most recruiters and employers say soft skills are equally as valuable most every work environment. So what exactly is the difference between hard and soft skills, and how are they relevant in recruitment and employment?<!--more--> We\'ve prepared a soft skills list so that you can use it to self-analyze and grow!\n<h2>Hard Skills vs. Soft Skills</h2>\n<strong>Hard skills</strong> refer to skills that are directly required for the job. They are the knowledge and abilities that are absolutely necessary and are easily quantifiable. Examples are typing, knowledge of specific software, basic accounting, and so on.\n\nOn the other hand, <strong>soft skills</strong> refer to abilities that pertain largely to an individual’s emotional quotient, communication skills, personality, and leadership skills. They focus more on a person’s strength of character rather than one’s formal work abilities. While these skills are mostly given significance in the customer service industry, they really are quite priceless in almost any business.\n\n<strong>To learn everything you need to know about developing your skills to get the job you want, check out our <a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/the-complete-step-by-step-guide-to-getting-a-job/\">Complete Step-by-Step Guide to Getting a Job</a>.</strong>\n<h2>Before We Jump Into the Soft Skills List...</h2>\nWe\'ve already emphasized the value of soft skills. Employers will love you for having excellent soft skills. So will your colleagues! To really start to improve on your soft skills, you must be able to self-analyze. Now, this doesn\'t mean you should criticize yourself. But what it does mean is that you should be able to acknowledge the areas that you need growth! Soft skills are hard to measure, and you will only grow to the extent that you are able to admit the areas where you\'re not perfect.\n\nNow, without further ado, our soft skills list.\n<h2>Excellent Communication</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>The ability to communicate clearly is indispensable in any workplace. Effective communication combines both nonverbal and verbal cues. To be able to express your thoughts, ideas, and emotions accurately and efficiently is a prerequisite for other skill sets like presentation skills, working with a team, and negotiating.</li>\n 	<li>Impress your recruiter or your boss by showing some active listening and using some gestures that support your ideas as you speak.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Adaptability and Flexibility</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>In a dynamic job market that is constantly changing, an employee has to be able to adjust and adapt to different situations. One should be able to look at change as an occasion to improve and learn. It is especially relevant when your company often transitions from one business objective to another. Adaptable employees are keen on new discoveries, which is vital for companies that need to stay ahead of their competition.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Critical Thinking and Decision-Making</h2>\n<ul>\n 	<li>Companies count on employees who are able to think rationally and independently. This allows them to trust that their employees can carry on with little supervision. Having high-level thinking skills will allow you to conceptualize, evaluate, persuade, negotiate and apply your ideas and beliefs. In business, it is imperative to be able to make choices that will be highly beneficial to the team.</li>\n 	<li>When it comes to these skills, it’s more efficient to show them than to tell them. During interviews for instance, when asked questions relating to your work experience, take the opportunity to showcase and imply your excellent soft skills by having one in mind as you answer the question. Review specific experiences and think deeply about which soft skills were applied in those situations. They sound more believable when recruiters hear about how you’ve applied them.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>The Last Word</h2>\nYou can hone these skills by taking classes or seminars for personality and character development.\n\nConsider seeking a <a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/how-to-make-the-most-of-your-job/\">mentor</a> who can coach you and offer a lot of practice time to cultivate your strengths. The thing about investing in soft skills is that they won’t just make you a better worker but a better person all around!','Soft Skills List: These Soft Skills Will Help You Succeed','We\'re here to explain the difference between hard and soft skills and how are they relevant in recruitment and employment?','publish','open','open','','soft-skills-find-job','','','2019-07-11 21:46:42','2019-07-11 21:46:42','',0,'http://www.finddreamjobs.com/?p=370',0,'post','',0),(381,2,'2016-03-11 16:59:48','2016-03-11 16:59:48','We’re here to offer you some interview tips and tricks that can help you snag that dream job right from the interview stage! We’ve gathered some tried and true advice from successful job seekers, seasoned recruiters, and top-notch employers. For more info check out our <a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/step-by-step-interview-guide/\">Step-by-Step Guide to Acing Your Interview</a>!<!--more-->\n<h2>Interview Tips</h2>\nFinding a job can already be extremely stressful. We want to make it as easy as possible to have the best possible odds of success in your job search. There are a broad variety of ways to help as you sit in front of your interviewer, answering their questions. However, the best possible interview tip for many of us is that a successful interview begins long before we ever arrive through the company\'s doors.\n<h3><strong>1. </strong>Have contacts within the company? Call them.</h3>\nGathering first-hand information from the people who are already in the company is the best move you can make. They are the premium resource for advice on the appropriate dress code, the typical interview process and company culture. Once you feel informed about these things, your confidence will naturally develop.\n\n<strong>Make sure you\'re prepared from A to Z for the job market with our <a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/the-complete-step-by-step-guide-to-getting-a-job/\">Complete Step-by-Step Guide to Getting a Job</a>.</strong>\n<h3>2. Clean up your profile.</h3>\nYes, we mean Facebook and other social media sites that the recruiters might check on anytime during the hiring process. You want to create an image that is consistent to one they’ll want on their team. It’s not just your resume that might be up for review, so you’ll want an equally pleasing social media profile, too. This interview tip is one that you should carry throughout your employment! It is common for employees to be terminated for what they post on their social media. Discretion is always a good idea.\n<h3>3. Research, research, research!</h3>\nOne of the best interview tips you can follow is to do your research. There are a wide variety of things you can research before your interview to improve your odds of success, but here are some of the best things to start with.\n\n<strong>The company: </strong>You applied for the job, but do you know anything about the company you applied for? For most employers, the hardest part of the job is finding employees who have a genuine interest in what the business does. Doing some initial research about the company and being able to refer to your knowledge during the interview can highlight you as a go-getter who is interested in the business and industry in general.\n\nCheck out the company on <a href=\"http://www.glassdoor.com\">Glassdoor</a> or by searching with Google!\n\n<strong>The Interviewer: </strong>It is common to know ahead of time to know who will be interviewing you. It is most definitely worth your while to check out the interviewer\'s social media, especially <a href=\"http://www.linkedin.com\">LinkedIn</a>, to get a sense of who they are and how to highlight your skills to them.\n\n<strong>The Industry: </strong>Whether you\'re applying for to be a local mechanic or a software developer, understanding the trends in your industry will set you apart. Try to know the company\'s competitors: how they do business and what they offer. This bit of research will allow you to explain to your future employer <em>why you want to work for them, and not for the other guys.</em>\n<h3>4. Know thy resume.</h3>\nEveryone knows their resume, you wrote it, right? While this is true, it is a very good practice to briefly review your resume before sitting down to interview with a prospective employer. Reviewing your resume beforehand will ensure that you\'ve written your resume to the highest possible standards. It will also prepare you for any potential questions that the employer will ask you.\n\n<a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/how-to-build-my-perfect-resume/\">Need help with your resume? Check out our extremely helpful guide on how to create a fantastic resume.</a>\n<h3>5. Personality matters. A lot.</h3>\nIt’s not just about your resume and work experience; the recruiters also want to know how your overall personality fits into the position. That’s why most of the initial questions include, “Will you please tell me about yourself?” You need to prepare to answer this question in a way that holistically describes your best self and not simply addressing what you think the job description demands. Consider mentioning a random anecdote or a funny experience - it will help break the ice and set the tone for the rest of the interview.\n<h3>6. Mirror their movements.</h3>\nMirroring the interviewer’s tone, volume and gestures is one way to subtly demonstrate that you are on the same page as they are. Remember to be subtle and discreet. There is a fine line between mirroring and mimicking. You want to suggest connection and sensitivity towards the person you are talking to.\n<h3>7. Connect with your interviewer.</h3>\nForge a bond with your interviewer by finding some common ground like an interest, cause or hobby you are both passionate about. This will make you easier to recall and remember when they have initially taken a general liking towards you in the beginning. Take time to focus on the person who is doing the interview and not just the employment at stake. Although this is one of the best interview tips, don\'t let it lead you astray! Remember to stay on topic and do not lead the conversation astray.\n<h3>8. Prepare your own list of questions.</h3>\nNothing says proactive and take-charge more than an engaged and inquisitive interviewee. Review the questions that are essential for you to know in order to find out if the position and the company are the best fit for you right now. This is a time for you to assess your employer as well.\n<h3>9. Always end with a strong closing statement.</h3>\nWith every question, answer with confidence and structure. The recruiter will be quick to pick up on anxiety and poor leadership skills if you end up rambling on and beating around the bush. Try to hit the target when you are asked; be sure to hit the main point first followed by strong supporting statements or examples. A great trick is to think in bullet points rather than a long-winding essay.','9 Interview Tips That Will Get You The Job!','We’re here to offer you some fast facts that can help you snag that dream job right from the interview stage! ','publish','open','open','','interview-tips','','','2019-07-11 21:46:49','2019-07-11 21:46:49','',0,'http://www.finddreamjobs.com/?p=381',0,'post','',0),(387,2,'2016-03-15 13:47:21','2016-03-15 13:47:21','<strong>Recruiters leaf through a countless set of cover letters each day and there are just a chosen few that get handpicked from the bunch. What gives? Here are a few cover letter tips on how to make your cover letter stand out in a positive way.</strong>\n\n<!--more-->\n<h2>What\'s a cover letter and why should you write one?</h2>\nA well-written cover letter should give you the opportunity to introduce yourself to the employer. For this reason, cover letters have been (and still are!) a hugely important part of the application process. A resume is great for showing your employer your qualifications, training, expertise, education, etc. In your cover letter, you should talk about:\n<ol>\n 	<li>Your interest in the job.</li>\n 	<li>Why you\'re interested.</li>\n 	<li>How you can impact their business.</li>\n 	<li>and more!</li>\n</ol>\nRead through our cover letter tips and start writing killer cover letters for your job applications.\n<h3>1. Customize your letter for each employer and position.</h3>\nAt this initial stage, the recruiter needs to see that you are the best fit for the job. One way to achieve this is to show that you have the necessary skills and experiences to fulfill the responsibilities of the job as defined in the job description. It’s not hard for a recruiter to spot a cover letter template. They will be able to differentiate easily between a generic cover letter that was sent to various employers versus one that was made with the intention of securing the specific position that their company is looking for. Think about using the same language and communication style as the company uses, which you can easily find on the job posting itself as well as on the company’s website. Any recruiter will appreciate a considerable effort that was thoroughly and thoughtfully given.\n<h3>2. State your purpose for writing.</h3>\nFirst, introduce yourself and mention the position you are applying for. Also, explain how you found out about the vacancy in detail. Next, it’s most important to state WHY you choose to work with the organization. Follow it up with how you can benefit the organization by filling in the post you are applying for. Be specific about how their mission and company values align with your own personal strengths.\n<h3>3. Your cover letter does what your resume cannot.</h3>\nA cover letter is not a narrative version of your resume. It’s pointless to repeat everything that appears in your resume. Think of your cover letter as a great space to include all of the additional qualifications that would make you a great candidate. Thoroughly explain how you can be an asset to the company and indicate soft skills that they might find valuable to the position.\n<h3>4. Be detail oriented, thorough, and specific!</h3>\nBe clear about what you want to say. Try to provide examples where they would be helpful. After you mention a soft skill, follow up with concrete experiences where you were able to exemplify it. Focus on being authentic and know your audience. You need to address the letter accordingly. Therefore, you must avoid using “To whom it may concern”. Proofread for errors and try to review your writing from the reader’s point-of-view. What would you revise?\n<h3>5. Aim for depth and relevance</h3>\nYour cover letter is a focused, well-thought-out document that summarizes your achievements and qualifications, but at the same time provides explanation and examples to give more meaning to your accomplishments. It should be able to support your resume by providing evidence that your work experience is absolutely going to help you succeed at the position you are applying for.\n\n<strong>Lastly, don’t forget to thank them for their time and do leave your contact information because we’re certain that they’ll be getting in touch soon!</strong>\n\nFor more, read our guide <a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/how-to-build-the-perfect-resume/\">How to Build the Perfect Resume</a>.\n<h2>Don\'t forget...</h2>\nAs mentioned previously in our Cover Letter Tips, each cover letter should be created specifically for the employer and the position you\'re seeking. Try to refrain from creating a template for your cover letters, but if you must, make sure to measure the results.\n\nAfter a round of applications, count the number of call-backs you receive. For the next round of applications, make edits to your cover letter and measure if it gets you more call-backs than your previous letter.','5 Essential Cover Letter Tips to Land Your Dream Job','','publish','open','open','','5-tips-for-your-cover-letter','','','2019-07-11 21:43:31','2019-07-11 21:43:31','',0,'http://www.finddreamjobs.com/?p=387',0,'post','',0),(469,2,'2016-04-28 19:43:59','2016-04-28 19:43:59','<p>If you just received an offer for your dream job, congratulations! The job-hunt may have been stressful but the first day on the job can sometimes feel like being the new kid in high school all over again. Here are some tips that can help you get a hold of your new work environment and overcome those employment jitters. You’ll transition much more smoothly if you come in well prepared.<!--more--></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/the-complete-step-by-step-guide-to-getting-a-job/\">Haven\'t found your Dream Job yet? Here\'s our complete guide on how to find a job that you love. </a></p>\n<h2>14 Tips on How to Successfully Start a New Job:</h2>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">1. Get some quality sleep the night before.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Starting the day well rested will help keep you in top form for the rest of the big day.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">2. Prepare an outfit beforehand.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Get a new one or put together your best pieces that will get you feeling confident and comfortable the whole day.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">3. Organize all the items that you need to take with you.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Don’t forget to be well equipped with much-needed supplies like a pen, notebook, and flash drive. Also, pack a good lunch or plan where to get a nutritious one over the break.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">4. Figure out the best way to get to the office to avoid stressing on the way.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Check the weather, too, so you can prepare appropriately!</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">5. Do some extensive research on the company culture.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Know what to expect from a typical work shift. Call someone who works there if you have a contact.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">6. Be punctual and arrive just a few minutes early.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Remember that you’ll need to get familiar with the schedule and the premises first.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">7. Listen attentively to any briefing that you will receive.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Talk to your boss or supervisor about their expectations of you, especially for the first few weeks. It will make a solid impression of being proactive and will help you organize your schedule at the same time.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">8. Be friendly and greet new people warmly and professionally.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Try to take note of their names and positions as much as you can. Also, remember to speak respectfully to everyone in the office! Go in with a \"treat the janitor as well as the CEO\" mentality.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">9. Be ready to absorb as much as you can.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Observe your surroundings and listen to any input that your coworkers have to say. This will help you establish your bearings much more efficiently.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">10. Ask questions along the way to get some much-needed direction.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Not only will asking questions help you learn your job faster, it will also show your employer that you\'re a go-getter that is passionately pursuing excellence at work. </p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">11. Be ready to manage your time efficiently.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Some managers will expect you to come ready to work hard on the first day. Make sure that you\'re also ready to work smart! </p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">12. Take your time when familiarizing with office equipment and systems.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Note down all your questions if they can’t be addressed right away so you can go back to them when an opportunity presents itself.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">13. Pace yourself at a level that you’re comfortable with.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">There’s no need to overstretch your limits trying to master everything all at once. It’s your first day after all, no one expects you to be at expert level right away.</p>\n<h3 style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">14. Get all the necessary contact information that you need, especially from those that you will be working closely with.</h3>\n<p style=\"padding-left: 40px;\">Securing their emails and phone numbers will make it possible to check with them if there’s anything you need urgent assistance with.</p>\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','How to Start a New Job with Confidence','','publish','open','open','','how-to-start-a-new-job','','','2019-07-11 21:47:01','2019-07-11 21:47:01','',0,'http://www.finddreamjobs.com/?p=469',0,'post','',0),(820,2,'2017-12-12 09:36:31','2017-12-12 09:36:31','','winter-landscape-2571788_1920','','inherit','open','closed','','winter-landscape-2571788_1920','','','2017-12-12 09:36:31','2017-12-12 09:36:31','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/winter-landscape-2571788_1920.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(886,2,'2017-12-12 20:45:07','2017-12-12 20:45:07','','jquery-logo','','inherit','open','closed','','jquery-logo','','','2017-12-12 20:45:07','2017-12-12 20:45:07','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/jquery-logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(887,2,'2017-12-12 20:45:08','2017-12-12 20:45:08','','mongo-db-logo','','inherit','open','closed','','mongo-db-logo','','','2017-12-12 20:45:08','2017-12-12 20:45:08','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mongo-db-logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(888,2,'2017-12-12 20:45:09','2017-12-12 20:45:09','','node-js-logo','','inherit','open','closed','','node-js-logo','','','2017-12-12 20:45:09','2017-12-12 20:45:09','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/node-js-logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(889,2,'2017-12-12 20:45:10','2017-12-12 20:45:10','','python-logo','','inherit','open','closed','','python-logo','','','2017-12-12 20:45:10','2017-12-12 20:45:10','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/python-logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(890,2,'2017-12-12 20:45:10','2017-12-12 20:45:10','','redis-logo','','inherit','open','closed','','redis-logo','','','2017-12-12 20:45:10','2017-12-12 20:45:10','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/redis-logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(891,2,'2017-12-12 20:45:11','2017-12-12 20:45:11','','ruby-logo','','inherit','open','closed','','ruby-logo','','','2017-12-12 20:45:11','2017-12-12 20:45:11','',0,'http://finddreamjobs.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/ruby-logo.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(1017,2,'2018-12-19 21:39:27','2018-12-19 21:39:27','<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"9a9n9-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"9a9n9-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"aolka-0-0\">Luckily for employees, it’s a buyers’ market. The economy is strong, and businesses are hiring like crazy! </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"aolka-1-0\">While it may seem like the high paying jobs are only available to people who decided to get a higher education, that could not be further from the truth</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"aolka-2-0\">. To prove it, we compiled a list of 11 of the highest paying jobs without a college degree. </span></div>\n</div>\n<!--more-->\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"5buj5-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"5buj5-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"5buj5-0-0\"> </span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-0-0\">Though some of these jobs may need some training or taking a class to hone your skills, you can bet it’ll pay off in the end. </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-1-0\"> According to the </span></span><a href=\"https://www.bls.gov/emp/tables/occupational-projections-and-characteristics.htm\"><span data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-2-0\">US Bureau of Labor Statistics</span></a><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-3-0\">, these are the highest paying jobs for those without a college degree</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-4-0\">. To prepare for your new job, check out our </span><a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/the-complete-step-by-step-guide-to-getting-a-job/\"><span data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-5-0\">Complete Step-by-Step Guide to Getting a Job</span></a><span data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-6-0\">.</span></div>\n<div data-offset-key=\"2qi2h-0-0\"></div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"fe1b2-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"fe1b2-0-0\">1. Transit and Railroad Police </span></h2>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"2mu4i-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"2mu4i-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"2mu4i-0-0\">These faithful police officers protect and watch railroad and transit property. </span><span data-offset-key=\"2mu4i-0-1\">They will also manage employees and passengers. The median wage is $66k and the job only requires a high school diploma or GED.</span> <span class=\"veryhardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"2mu4i-1-0\">While there are limits to the growth of railroad tracks and stations, with infrastructure plans on the horizon about 400 new jobs should be opening in the next 7 years</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"2mu4i-2-0\">. This highest paying job without a college degree ensures you plenty of exercise!</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"b0sc0-0-0\">\n<div data-offset-key=\"b0sc0-0-0\"></div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"b0sc0-0-0\">2. Gaming Managers</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"7uvmp-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"7uvmp-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"7uvmp-0-0\">Gaming managers manage the behind-the-scenes section of casinos. These managers plan, direct, and coordinate gaming operations. Which means they are the ones deciding which tables are open to gamblers, what the </span><span class=\"complexword\"><span data-offset-key=\"7uvmp-1-0\">minimum</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"7uvmp-2-0\"> is, and more. </span><span data-offset-key=\"7uvmp-2-1\">They usually make about $69k per year with a high school diploma.</span> <span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"7uvmp-3-0\">The prediction is that these jobs will explode with the legalization of gambling in many states</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"7uvmp-4-0\">. You do need some experience but can qualify for this job in less than five years!</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"51cio-0-0\">\n<div data-offset-key=\"51cio-0-0\"></div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"51cio-0-0\">3. Elevator Installers or Repairers</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"dlif1-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"dlif1-0-0\"><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"dlif1-0-0\">Like gaming managers, elevator installers and repairers are the magic behind the scenes as well</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"dlif1-1-0\">. </span><span data-offset-key=\"dlif1-1-1\">In this career, with only a high school diploma, you can earn $78k.</span> <span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"dlif1-2-0\">As more high-rises pop up in metropolitan areas, the need for these positions will likely grow 12% in the next 8 years</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"dlif1-3-0\">. Like most of the highest paying jobs without a college degree, this job has ups and downs. (Excuse the elevator joke!) </span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"6iu53-0-0\">\n<div data-offset-key=\"6iu53-0-0\"></div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"6iu53-0-0\">4. Claims Adjusters, Examiners, and Investigators</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"avq2h-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"avq2h-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"avq2h-0-0\">These more modern-day detectives make $64k per year on average. </span><span data-offset-key=\"avq2h-0-1\">They earn their paycheck by investigating different types of insurance claims. While this isn’t a growing field, these jobs are a constant. Working full time for the right company could mean full benefits and a 401k!</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"47agg-0-0\">\n<div data-offset-key=\"47agg-0-0\"></div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"47agg-0-0\">5. Executive Secretaries or Executive Assistants</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"clhli-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"clhli-0-0\"><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"clhli-0-0\">If you love working with the high energy people and you are an organized person, this could be a perfect position for you</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"clhli-1-0\">. Executive secretaries and executive assistants don’t need any specialized skills. Which means a high school diploma will get you into an interview room! </span><span data-offset-key=\"clhli-1-1\">The average salary is $57k per year.</span><span data-offset-key=\"clhli-1-2\"> But you may have to work your way up from a typical secretary position to the executive level. There are almost 700,000 executive assistants right now and these jobs aren’t going anywhere.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"c2qi6-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"c2qi6-0-0\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"dlkqt-0-0\">\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"dlkqt-0-0\">6. Power Plant Operators</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"8pp11-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"8pp11-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"8pp11-0-0\">Power plant operators control, operate and maintain machinery to generate electric power. This includes auxiliary equipment operators. As nuclear power demands grow, so do openings for these positions – in fact, up to 4,000 over the next few years. </span><span data-offset-key=\"8pp11-0-1\">All that you need is a high school diploma (or </span><span class=\"complexword\"><span data-offset-key=\"8pp11-1-0\">equivalent</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"8pp11-2-0\">) and you could find yourself making $74k per year. </span><span data-offset-key=\"8pp11-2-1\">It does involve some constant on-the-job training, but better to be safe than sorry!</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"as945-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"as945-0-0\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"5eruh-0-0\">\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"5eruh-0-0\">7. Transportation, Storage, Distribution Center Managers</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"a8m4f-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"a8m4f-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"a8m4f-0-0\">These managers coordinate transportation, storage, or distribution activities. They manage according to organizational policies and applicable government laws or regulations. As Amazon grows, so does the demand for managers to oversee the distribution centers. </span><span data-offset-key=\"a8m4f-0-1\">You only need a high school diploma and you can be making $89k a year or more!</span><span data-offset-key=\"a8m4f-0-2\"> While you may need to work your way up the food chain, you only need 5 years of experience.</span></div>\n<div data-offset-key=\"a8m4f-0-0\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"4ouis-0-0\">\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"4ouis-0-0\">8. Web Developers</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"f1k7f-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"f1k7f-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"f1k7f-0-0\">Web developers design, create and update websites. Whether that means working for an agency or in-house for a big company, developers are in high demand. Luckily, as long as you can code, it doesn’t matter what level of education you have! </span><span data-offset-key=\"f1k7f-0-1\">Median annual salary is $66k with the potential to make more.</span><span data-offset-key=\"f1k7f-0-2\"> Because digital is exploding right now, there will be 14,000 job openings over the next 6 years.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"alduc-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"alduc-0-0\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"ck3a5-0-0\">\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"ck3a5-0-0\">9. Subway and Streetcar Operators</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"eadbq-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"eadbq-0-0\"><span class=\"veryhardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"eadbq-0-0\">These operators work on subways or elevated suburban trains with no separate locomotive, or electric-powered streetcar, to transport passengers</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"eadbq-1-0\">. From what we can tell, it’s almost like playing a video game…except in real life. </span><span data-offset-key=\"eadbq-1-1\">The average salary is $64k per year for high school grads</span><span data-offset-key=\"eadbq-1-2\">. But current projections are that there will be over 1000 openings in the next 8 years. While you do need on-the-job training, you should be up and running (or driving!) in no time.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"d6e40-0-0\">\n<div data-offset-key=\"d6e40-0-0\"></div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"d6e40-0-0\">10. Postal service mail sorters, processors, and processing machine operators</h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"foc1d-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"foc1d-0-0\"><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"foc1d-0-0\">Ever wonder what work goes into getting your mail from point A to point B? Get a job as a postal service processor and learn all the secrets</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"foc1d-1-0\">! </span><span data-offset-key=\"foc1d-1-1\">These workers make $57k per year – with great government benefits. </span><span data-offset-key=\"foc1d-1-2\">And you only need a high school diploma or </span><span class=\"complexword\"><span data-offset-key=\"foc1d-2-0\">equivalent</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"foc1d-3-0\"> to get an interview.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"78sv5-0-0\">\n<div data-offset-key=\"78sv5-0-0\"></div>\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"78sv5-0-0\"><span style=\"color: #23282d; font-size: 1.6em; font-weight: 600;\">11. Electrical Power Line Maintenance </span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"6q233-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"6q233-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"6q233-0-0\">These technicians install, replace, and repair electrical lines. Because of these techs, our power grid is chugging along. </span><span data-offset-key=\"6q233-0-1\">You don’t need higher education to train for this job and operators make an average of $63k per year.</span><span data-offset-key=\"6q233-0-2\"> As population grows, estimates are that this job market will grow by 1,600 positions!</span></div>\n</div>','11 of the Highest Paying Jobs Without a College Degree','','publish','open','open','','11-of-the-highest-paying-jobs-you-can-get-without-a-college-degree','','','2019-07-11 21:47:08','2019-07-11 21:47:08','',0,'http://www.finddreamjobs.com/?p=1017',0,'post','',0),(1025,2,'2018-12-19 21:57:02','2018-12-19 21:57:02','<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"9a9n9-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"9a9n9-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"fgcmt-0-0\">Soft skills are more important now than ever before. As you apply to jobs or switching careers, you\'ve learned that the job market is competitive. </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"fgcmt-1-0\">There are a variety of essential soft skills that every job-seeker should master throughout their careers</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"fgcmt-2-0\">. Here\'s our list of soft skills for you to focus on - they\'ll help you to find your dream job! </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"fgcmt-3-0\">To learn everything you need to know about how to get a new job or your next job, read our </span></span><a href=\"https://www.finddreamjobs.com/guides/the-complete-step-by-step-guide-to-getting-a-job/\"><span data-offset-key=\"fgcmt-4-0\">Complete Step-by-Step Guide to Getting a Job</span></a><span data-offset-key=\"fgcmt-5-0\">.</span></div>\n<div data-offset-key=\"9a9n9-0-0\"></div>\n</div>\n<!--more-->\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"7lud4-0-0\">\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"7lud4-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"7lud4-0-0\">Why should you care about soft skills? </span></h2>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"akqea-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"akqea-0-0\"><span class=\"veryhardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"akqea-0-0\">Due to economic shifts, industry trends, and technological developments, the skills that employers look for in new hires are </span></span><span class=\"adverb\"><span data-offset-key=\"akqea-1-0\">constantly</span></span><span class=\"veryhardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"akqea-2-0\"> changing</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"akqea-3-0\">. </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"akqea-4-0\">Always be learning new things and expanding your skill set to maintain a competitive edge</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"akqea-5-0\">. Because there are some skills that will really help you stand out from the crowd. They\'ll help you catch the attention of a hiring manager or future employer:</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"5vjc7-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"5vjc7-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"5vjc7-0-0\"> </span></div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"fggam-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"fggam-0-0\">Problem Solving</span></h2>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"bv904-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"bv904-0-0\"><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"bv904-0-0\">An analytical mind is crucial to identify and resolve problems that arise in the workplace</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"bv904-1-0\">. It is important to be able to think on your feet and approach issues in a rational and level-headed manner. Show your hiring manager that you are good under pressure. </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"bv904-2-0\">During your job interview, prepare yourself to share concrete examples of the steps you’ve taken to overcome past challenges</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"bv904-3-0\">.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"80o80-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"80o80-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"80o80-0-0\"> </span></div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"3m1q2-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"3m1q2-0-0\">Communication</span></h2>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"a4so4-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"a4so4-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"a4so4-0-0\">Good communication skills are a must for any job. When sharing ideas and information, consider the format which you share. Remember to adjust your tone (and format) to appeal to the audience. Make sure all written and verbal communications are as clear and concise as possible. The more </span><span class=\"adverb\"><span data-offset-key=\"a4so4-1-0\">efficiently</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"a4so4-2-0\"> you communicate with others, the easier it will be to execute on a project plan. Efficient communication will ensure that all parties involved understand the task at hand. Individuals with strong communication skills will gain respect and authority in the workplace.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"85dob-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"85dob-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"85dob-0-0\"> </span></div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"f7g5n-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"f7g5n-0-0\">Collaboration</span></h2>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"30udn-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"30udn-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"30udn-0-0\">No matter what your position, starting a new job will need you to be a team player. </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"30udn-1-0\">Be able to communicate your own ideas in an effective manner and prepare to listen to input from your coworkers</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"30udn-2-0\">. Cross-team initiatives are fantastic opportunities to build relationships with colleagues. Approach these initiatives with an open mind, they\'ll usually benefit your career! Don’t be afraid to ask for help or offer up your own skills as a resource to support others in need of a helping hand.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"5b81e-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"5b81e-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"5b81e-0-0\"> </span></div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"csjdr-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"csjdr-0-0\">Digital Literacy</span></h2>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"80qvn-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"80qvn-0-0\"><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"80qvn-0-0\">It is almost impossible to function in the workplace without some knowledge of the digital tools that shape our everyday lives</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"80qvn-1-0\">.  Prove competency in social media by maintaining a clean, professional profile on platforms. Employers may visit your Facebook, Twitter, and LinkedIn. </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"80qvn-2-0\">You cannot afford to act in an inappropriate or unprofessional manner on social media</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"80qvn-3-0\">. </span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"2ajg7-0-0\">\n<h3 data-offset-key=\"2ajg7-0-0\">Softwares</h3>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"3cjp0-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"3cjp0-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"3cjp0-0-0\">You must have knowledge of word processing tools like Microsoft Word. Spreadsheet programs such as Microsoft Excel are also of vital importance. Use them to organize &amp; analyze important information or data. Once you\'ve learned how to apply these skills, list them on your resume with pride. Beyond these programs, learn how to use your email! An organized inbox will make your professional life much simpler. </span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"ckko5-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"ckko5-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"ckko5-0-0\"> </span></div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"7a29o-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"7a29o-0-0\">Adaptability</span></h2>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"763s9-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"763s9-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"763s9-0-0\">Like everything else in this world, there are no guarantees in the workplace. Management can shift, or new tasks may become your responsibility. It is important to be flexible and receptive to change. Look at each bump in the road as an opportunity to grow, rather than a setback. Do not resist organizational or cultural changes, but rather grow with them. Prove that you can step up and thrive in an evolving work environment. Make sure to expand your own skill set as the company grows and transforms.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"75l5f-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"75l5f-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"75l5f-0-0\"> </span></div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"6t7co-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"6t7co-0-0\">Time Management</span></h2>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"41gmb-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"41gmb-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-0-0\">The ability to work in an efficient manner is key to any fast-paced work environment. Prove to your employer that you know how to </span><span class=\"complexword\"><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-1-0\">prioritize</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-2-0\"> your work. Then make good use of the time for your projects. </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-3-0\">Make sure to keep track of deadlines and avoid leaving tasks to the last minute whenever possible</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-4-0\">. </span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-5-0\">When you arrive at a job interview, also be ready to discuss some of the tactics you use to </span></span><span class=\"complexword\"><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-6-0\">prioritize</span></span><span class=\"hardreadability\"><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-7-0\"> your work and complete projects in a timely fashion</span></span><span data-offset-key=\"41gmb-8-0\">.</span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"\" data-block=\"true\" data-editor=\"ee8ud\" data-offset-key=\"cub1u-0-0\">\n<div class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"cub1u-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"cub1u-0-0\"> </span></div>\n</div>\n<h2 class=\"public-DraftStyleDefault-block public-DraftStyleDefault-ltr\" data-offset-key=\"7as04-0-0\"><span data-offset-key=\"7as04-0-0\">Work Ethic</span></h2>\nMany people think that you either have a good work ethic, or you don\'t. However, those of us who are able to work very hard for long periods of time were trained by someone to do that. That responsibility (probably) fell on your parents or teachers. But many of us either didn\'t learn or were never properly instructed.\n\nTake some time to self-analyze. Do you recognize a bit of laziness in yourself? Is the answer \'yes?\' Going forward, become more aware of this trait within yourself. Often, simple awareness of our problems can help to bring a solution!\n<h2>Other Soft Skills</h2>\nThere is a multitude of soft skills beyond those that we\'ve listed here. From the ability to manage stress, maintain a healthy work/life balance, and much more. While soft skills may not seem like a priority to you, they absolutely should be. The reason why is: soft skills apply to your professional life and your personal life. Take the time to invest in learning soft skills and reap the rewards.\n\nInterested in reading more about soft skills? <a href=\"https://www.goskills.com/Soft-Skills\">Here\'s a guide that we found helpful.</a>','8 Soft Skills Essential for Today\'s Job Market','','publish','open','open','','essential-soft-skills','','','2019-07-11 21:48:11','2019-07-11 21:48:11','',0,'http://www.finddreamjobs.com/?p=1025',0,'post','',0),(2137,2,'2017-12-18 14:49:00','2017-12-18 14:49:00','','whos-this-for','','inheri